{"questionId":"3514692","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Ani opens an office equidistant from three of the cafes, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math>. The equation of the perpendicular bisector of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>[</mo><mi>BC</mi><mo>]</mo></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the coordinates of the office.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to solve simultaneous equations: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04545</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86363</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04545</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86363</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math> in place of coordinates.</p>\n<p>Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>87</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>85</mn><mo>)</mo></math>) for using their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> sf or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math> sf <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-value to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> from any of the two equations.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3514692","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ2.7c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the coordinates of the office.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Intersection of lines, equations of perpendicular bisectors","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Voronoi diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}